				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What level can we charm?<a name="70619"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 4 04 1:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't have it yet, but Lucy's gives max level 68. Could be &lt;= 68 or &lt; 68.
<br />

<br />
Calling it useless is just absurd. Just because you can't swarm kite, there are many other uses for charm. It gives you another option for handling adds. Some extra dps. And the mob doesn't have to be mezzed, beating on someone else would do. Way back when, I used to use charm to regain aggro. Solo'ing you can kill two mobs at once faster than chanting by itself (even if your pet is the first to die, you were going to kill him anyway). 
<br />

<br />
A trade off had to be made. They were not going to let us swarmkite at 70. Give it up. I'm happy with this approach. Because it means we can have a real charm again. Without the short range, we wouldn't have a viable charm at all. It would probably be capped at about 62. There will be those brave souls who swarm even with the 30 range, but not that many with the increased risk and slower going. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
