				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What level can we charm?<a name="70838"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 10 04 2:59 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, while I agree that the amount of mana needed and the range of the song is a bad combo, this song is far from useless just as these guys have said.  No, I don't have this song yet, but I use the lvl 64 charm all the time, and not just when I can cast from max range.
<br />

<br />
Solo XP
<br />
1. You say the problem is that pet is horrid DPS and owned by anything you throw at it.  Have you tried to slow the target you throw pet at and leave pet alone?
<br />
2. I thought the way we used previous charms anyway, was reverse charming, send in 1 till it's near death, go invis, then finish off pet or charm something else to kill it for you.  How many bards farmed xp in PoNightmares reverse charming hobgobbies?  15 gobbies down in 5min or less is pretty quick xp at 64/65.
<br />

<br />
Group XP -- I think this is where the song would be at its most powerful.  
<br />
1. Now I realize that bards are not going to be called on as MT in groups 99% of the time, but that does NOT mean we are just wearing paper plate that crumples in 2 hits.  And unfortunately with certain bugs/nerfs bards have only 1 way to grab aggro now.  Charm.  Your MT just went down and the creature is thinking your cleric looks REALLY tastey, you could mez it and let your group recover then re-engage, or you could try to quickly finish it off because it only has 15% left.  Charm it, then invis, and go to town trying to finish it off.  You do get deftdance for a reason you know...
<br />
2. Why worry about mezzing a creature and trying to sing mele/regen and attacking other creature and the hassle of switching targets, turning attack on and off, when you can try to charm it and just mele/buff as normal?  Granted not being a fixed duration can suck, but unless this charm is a huge change from the previous 2 charms, it should last 18sec easy with decent cha, so you still get at least a small break.  
<br />

<br />
I realize that this isn't the same, but I use DC type pets in Sol Ro or other zones when in groups semi often now because they won't just kill me instantly and 90mana is usually regen'd by the time it breaks (FT6), so it's not a huge hassle for easily doubling my DPS.  I know this isn't the same with new charm because of the higher mana cost, and the higher risk for when the pet breaks free, but then again your not just doubling your DPS, chances are you would be quadrupling it with a good pet, so every now and then this would rock (like killing named guys).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
